ratings.question_text: What is your overall assessment of this course?

narratives.question_text: How would you summarize AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 for a fellow student? Would you recommend AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: Tough material at times but the lectures are always interesting the the professor has contagious enthusiasm for the material.
I would recommend it with the proviso that it's probably a course worth doing if you have less than a full load and expect to be able to devote a good deal of time and energy.

narratives.question_text: How did this course deepen your knowledge of your discipline/profession? To what extent did this course contribute to your dissertation/research?
comments: Helped me have a much better understanding of why these questions appeal to linguists, and what Chomsky was doing that was so different from what had been done. I don't love the material. But I see why some do.
I've already used reapplied of the methods and language from the course and do feel better for having done it.
